"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is trying to plot date values on the x-axis, but Matplotlib requires these dates to be converted to a format it can understand. The code also tries to use datetime.datetime.strptime to place a text on the plot, but this will throw an error because strptime returns a datetime object, but plot is using datetime objects as x values and integer values as y values.\",\n  \"patch\": \"15c15\\n< ax.plot(df['C'], df['E'])\\n---\\n> ax.plot_date(df['C'], df['E'])\\n17c17\\n< plt.text(datetime.datetime.strptime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\"), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n---\\n> plt.text(datetime.datetime.strptime(\\\"2013-01-05\\\", \\\"%Y-%m-%d\\\"), 0.5, \\\"SAMPLE\\\")\\n> ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(plt.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))\\n> fig.autofmt_xdate()\"\n}"